1. Grade Checker
File Name: Score.py
This program will take input from the user and share the grade based on predefined conditions.

90 and above A
80-89 B
70-79 C
60-69 D
Below 60 F

Concepts Used
- if-elif-else conditions
- User input handling

2. Store Grade 
This program uses a dictionary to store student names, age and their grades. It allows users to:
- Add a new student
- Update an existing student's grade
- View all student records

Concepts Used
- Python dictionaries
- Loops (while)
- Conditional statements

3. Combined Read/Write Program
Description
A menu-driven program that allows users to:

- Write content to a file
- Read content from a file
- Exit the program

Features
- User-friendly interface
- Error handling for missing files
- Uses with open() for safe file operations

Concepts Used
- Loops and conditionals
- File handling
- Exception handling (try-except)